  "detailed_description": "<p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><i>Going Your Own Way</i> is a visual novel that allows you to make choices that will help a young man trying to understand his place in the world while dealing with the recent ending of a long-term relationship, the challenges of modern dating, and a toxic workplace. </p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >This isn't a fantasy.  You aren't wealthy or famous.  You aren't an expert with the ladies or extraordinarily buff.  You are fairly average and were leading a pretty average life until you took your fiancée to a tropical island only to return alone. </p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><span class=\"bb_img_ctn\"><img class=\"bb_img\" src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/3247540/extras/59107aa4c4c0f55dfee8ffbed57cc177.avif?t=1771014568\" data-big-src=https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/3247540/extras_big/59107aa4c4c0f55dfee8ffbed57cc177.avif?t=1771014568 width=800 height=450 /></span></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >Now you are picking up the pieces and trying to move on as best you can.  You work an increasingly frustrating corporate desk job.  You rent an apartment you can no longer afford by yourself.  Sometimes you are lonely; sometimes you can't stand people. </p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><span class=\"bb_img_ctn\"><img class=\"bb_img\" src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/3247540/extras/bb62a15226a82f64ebd6bdfd9f215398.avif?t=1771014568\" data-big-src=https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/3247540/extras_big/bb62a15226a82f64ebd6bdfd9f215398.avif?t=1771014568 width=800 height=450 /></span></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" > </p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >In this story, you will visit not-so-exotic places such as your office, the gym, local bars, restaurants, and coffee shops.  What path do you want to take?</p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >Want to stay in shape?  Maybe visit the gym.</p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><span class=\"bb_img_ctn\"><img class=\"bb_img\" src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/3247540/extras/a2b526d3a84393021753016d36db4d3a.avif?t=1771014568\" data-big-src=https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/3247540/extras_big/a2b526d3a84393021753016d36db4d3a.avif?t=1771014568 width=800 height=450 /></span></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" > </p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >Want to meet someone?  Perhaps check out the bar scene.</p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><span class=\"bb_img_ctn\"><img class=\"bb_img\" src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/3247540/extras/b0df12f2465d41fe7f3bc81237b2322e.avif?t=1771014568\" data-big-src=https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/3247540/extras_big/b0df12f2465d41fe7f3bc81237b2322e.avif?t=1771014568 width=800 height=450 /></span></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" > </p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >Maybe after a long day at work, you just want to head home, play video games, and be alone.</p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><span class=\"bb_img_ctn\"><img class=\"bb_img\" src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/3247540/extras/4e6a6c60aae9f3a349684172e8af251e.avif?t=1771014568\" data-big-src=https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/3247540/extras_big/4e6a6c60aae9f3a349684172e8af251e.avif?t=1771014568 width=800 height=450 /></span></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" > </p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >You will meet and interact with people – some good and some... less so.  What are the rewards or consequences for how you treat people?  The choice is yours.</p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><span class=\"bb_img_ctn\"><img class=\"bb_img\" src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/3247540/extras/2f1097635264ee85506e64df41a92ac3.avif?t=1771014568\" data-big-src=https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/3247540/extras_big/2f1097635264ee85506e64df41a92ac3.avif?t=1771014568 width=800 height=450 /></span></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" > </p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >What does your future hold for you? Should you take advice from friends and family?</p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >Are you a relationship guy who wants to hold out to meet someone special, or are you lonely and willing to just settle for your turn with someone to avoid being alone?</p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><span class=\"bb_img_ctn\"><img class=\"bb_img\" src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/3247540/extras/de675c0d8d30afb33b5e2975bb350a75.avif?t=1771014568\" data-big-src=https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/3247540/extras_big/de675c0d8d30afb33b5e2975bb350a75.avif?t=1771014568 width=800 height=450 /></span></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" > </p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >Maybe you are the type that prefers to avoid people or relationships altogether and instead be a man who goes his own way?</p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><i>Going Your Own Way</i> pokes fun at the modern dating environment, relationships, and corporate workplace. </p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><span class=\"bb_img_ctn\"><img class=\"bb_img\" src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/3247540/extras/66e47b39539f1cca50675f45d0815f81.avif?t=1771014568\" data-big-src=https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/3247540/extras_big/66e47b39539f1cca50675f45d0815f81.avif?t=1771014568 width=800 height=450 /></span></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >Do you lean blue-pill or red-pill?  Will your view of the real-world influence your decisions? </p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><i>Going Your Own Way – Episode One</i> introduces the characters and lays the foundation for the story to come.</p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><strong>Episode One</strong> <strong>Features:</strong></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >2,800+ images.</p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >24,000+ words.</p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >Multiple decision paths that will influence future episodes. </p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >Created using Ren'Py and Daz Studio.</p>",
  "about_the_game": "<p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><i>Going Your Own Way</i> is a visual novel that allows you to make choices that will help a young man trying to understand his place in the world while dealing with the recent ending of a long-term relationship, the challenges of modern dating, and a toxic workplace. </p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >This isn't a fantasy.  You aren't wealthy or famous.  You aren't an expert with the ladies or extraordinarily buff.  You are fairly average and were leading a pretty average life until you took your fiancée to a tropical island only to return alone. </p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><span class=\"bb_img_ctn\"><img class=\"bb_img\" src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/3247540/extras/59107aa4c4c0f55dfee8ffbed57cc177.avif?t=1771014568\" data-big-src=https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/3247540/extras_big/59107aa4c4c0f55dfee8ffbed57cc177.avif?t=1771014568 width=800 height=450 /></span></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >Now you are picking up the pieces and trying to move on as best you can.  You work an increasingly frustrating corporate desk job.  You rent an apartment you can no longer afford by yourself.  Sometimes you are lonely; sometimes you can't stand people. </p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><span class=\"bb_img_ctn\"><img class=\"bb_img\" src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/3247540/extras/bb62a15226a82f64ebd6bdfd9f215398.avif?t=1771014568\" data-big-src=https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/3247540/extras_big/bb62a15226a82f64ebd6bdfd9f215398.avif?t=1771014568 width=800 height=450 /></span></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" > </p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >In this story, you will visit not-so-exotic places such as your office, the gym, local bars, restaurants, and coffee shops.  What path do you want to take?</p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >Want to stay in shape?  Maybe visit the gym.</p><p class=\"bb_parag